quran[19]{c,v,t}:
  73,1,You who are bundled up
  73,2,"stay up all night, except for a little while"
  73,3,half of it or a trifle less than that
  73,4,"or [even] add some to it, and chant the Quran distinctly as it should be chanted"
  73,5,We will cast a weighty statement on you
  73,6,"The onset of night is more serious for impressions, as well as more effective for speaking in"
  73,7,You have lengthy employment during daylight
  73,8,Mention your LordÂ´s name and devote yourself to Him utterly
  73,9,"Lord of the East and the West, there is no deity except Him, so accept him as your Defender"
  73,10,"Be patient about anything they may say, and steer clear of them in a polite manner"
  73,11,Let Me deal with rejectors who are enjoying their leisure; put up with them for a while
  73,12,Before us there lie fetters and Hades
  73,13,"plus food which will make you choke, and painful torment"
  73,14,"Some day the earth and mountains will rumble, and the mountains spill over as if they had been turned into sand"
  73,15,"We have sent a messenger to you (all) to act as a witness concerning you, just as We sent Pharaoh a messenger"
  73,16,"Yet Pharaoh defied the messenger, so We seized him mercilessly"
  73,17,So how will you do your duty if you already disbelieve in the day which will turn children into greybeards
  73,18,The sky will crack open from it; His promise will be fulfilled
  73,19,"This is a Reminder, so let anyone who so wishes, adopt a way unto his Lord"